commit.message: src/enchant.c: When we only output the parameter -h, the return value should be 0
configure.ac: bump version to 2.6.8
'Fess up about lack of Enchant user-directory dictionary support
Aspell: update note about aspell_dict_info_list_size

GitHub CI: drop Win32 build

nuspell is no longer built for Win32, it seems. Rather than complicate the
build, see if anyone cares enough to ask for it to be reinstated.
enchant.5: remove outdated information about hunspell provider
Bump version to 2.6.7 and add NEWS
Ensure GError is initialized to NULL in hunspell provider (fix #356)
Add NEWS for 2.6.6
configure.ac: bump version to 2.6.6

Fix paths used for reading configuration files

There were a few problems here:

* Neither pkgdatadir nor sysconfdir were used with the version suffix in
  libenchant.
* The use of sysconfdir (/etc) was not documented in enchant(5)
* enchant(5) showed an unversioned path for pkgdatadir (/usr/share).
* (PKG)DATADIR was not substituted into enchant.5, but left as literal text.
Add more debug logging, mainly for attempts to read config files
NEWS: add a note for the next version about DICPATH (see #354)
Makefile.am: in release target, checkout doxygen directory to avoid spurious diffs
Makefile.am: in release target, push commits and tags in one command
Add NEWS for removal of --with-PROVIDER-dir configure flags

Remove mostly-bogus --with-*-dir configure options (fix #352)

The only one that had any effect was --with-hunspell-dir. Remove its
implementation. Hunspell users can either use DICPATH, or place dictionaries
in the standard Enchant user directory.
Hunspell: ignore irrelevant C++ warning
Add Doxygen documentation to git, so it will be shown on website
Bump version to 2.6.5 and add NEWS

Add Doxygen documentation to release tarball (fix #183)

Need to upgrade the tarball format to POSIX 1003.1-1988.
README: small language tweak

Add debug logging of provider error messages

Also fold enchant_broker_set_error into its only caller. The function itself
did not check its arguments, but its caller does.

enchant: print error message when a dictionary is not available

As in enchant-lsmod. Use the same wording as there (its better).

Allow error messages to be invalid UTF-8 (fix #350)

Sometimes the invalid character is the problem.

Add a warning message to the API documentation.
enchant.h: consistently spell the encoding UTF-8 not sometimes UTF8
configure.ac: bump version to 2.6.4 and add NEWS
GitHub: update checkout action to v4

Make pkgdatadir a versioned directory by default

Hence, by default install enchant.ordering in /usr/share/enchant-2

Defaulting to /usr/share/enchant was simply not useful, as most packaging
systems require files in parallel packages to be distinct.

configure.ac: add version check for UnitTest++

https://github.com/msys2/MINGW-packages/issues/17297 is now fixed.
